[2]
Date: Mon 11 Jul 2011
From: Andrew Voas <andrew.voas@scotland.gsi.gov.uk> [edited]


As a point of information I believe it is widely accepted that
dingoes were introduced to mainland Australia by humans several
thousand years ago and that this preceded the extinction of the devil
on the Australian mainland about 3000 years ago. For example there is
a paper on the origin of the dingo obtained from the study of
mitochondrial DNA at http://www.pnas.org/content/101/33/12387.full

